<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-751DA270-7A23-4127-84D1-1D576534E948" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-751DA270-7A23-4127-84D1-1D576534E948" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Extended installation wizard (skip/re-execute) (R 4.4 and higher)</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M148553-B105"><p class="- topic/p ">With the extended installation wizard also the engine calibrations are executed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> For some scenarios it is helpful to execute only a part of the steps of the installation wizard. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Patches are created to enable or skip steps of the installation wizard. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Patches can be found on the SFT site:<xref class="- topic/xref " format="htm" href="https://sftexternal.cpp.canon/EFTClient/Account/Login.htm" scope="external"><?ditaot gentext?>https://sftexternal.cpp.canon/EFTClient/Account/Login.htm</xref> in the following location: CMXX\Patches. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The patches can only be installed once. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-D04FE361-B34A-4779-B5A6-17C4C1A38F67" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Patches</title><table id="GUID-C4D6CBD5-F096-40AD-9975-245F98B9A194" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Patch description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Name of patch 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">When installed in setting editor 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Skip the printhead, engine calibration and license configuration 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> In case of an install of the controller without a backup restored (HDD replacement, Clean install). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">First follow the wizard until the ip address is known. Via the settings editor apply the patch and manually force a restart. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Restoring a backup has the same effect. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Re-enable all the controller steps of the wizard.
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The controller section of the wizard will be re-executed completely.
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> IW_ActivateAllSteps.exe 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i "> ReenableR4InstallWizard</i> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Re-enable all the engine related calibration steps of the calibration wizard.
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">To re-execute the printhead and engine calibrations; enter SDS mode; start SDS test “<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">21-6-002 Select required printer calibrations [Special Tests]</b>”. Select calibrations “-- 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">All calibrations needed (set all)</b> –” and exit the SDS session. 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Note: 
</b>The printhead calibrations are not executed. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-9F558A57-CA95-4704-B153-815EC44AC177" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-7D3F358C-1AB9-4A5D-9B0E-C75D689F152E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
